The Revolution Will Not Be Televised;;92;;98;;NC;;In April 2002, the democratically elected Venezuelan president, Hugo Chavez, faces a coup d'état by an American-backed opposition party. The two-day coup fails to topple Chávez, but the tumultuous event proves to be great dramatic material for two Irish filmmakers who happen to be making a documentary about Chavez as the coup erupts. They capture footage of the massive opposition and pro-Chavez crowds and analyze how Venezuelan TV manipulated images for propaganda purposes.;;Documentary;;Kim Bartley,Donnacha O'Briain;;2003;;Hugo Chavez;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/chavez_inside_the_coup